Eskom announced that Stage 2 load shedding will continue in Vhembe until Sunday, 23 February. The schedule for the weekend is as follows: SATURDAY 22 FEBRUARY Areas: Louis Trichardt, Levubu, Valdezia, Elim Areas, Waterval, Chavani, Ximausa, Vleifontein, Blinkwater and Rotterdam, Mashau, Vuwani Areas, Nesengani, Madombidzha Areas and Sinthumule Areas. From 01:00 to 03:30 and
From 09:00 to 11:30 Areas: Tshakhuma, Lwamondo, Shayandima, Muledane, Thohoyandou, Sibasa, Ngovhela, Phiphidi, Gondeni, Vhufuli, Vondwe, Makonde, Tshikweta, Thengwe, Sanari, Makuya, Masisi, Malale, Madimbo, Muswodi and all Mutale Areas. From 03:00 to 05:30 and
From 11:00 to 13:30 Areas: Mukondeni, Mashamba, Tshivhuyuni, Mulima, Nthabalala,Tshitale, Muwaweni, Mbhokota, Riverplats, Botlokwa, Soekmekaar. From 05:00 to 07:30 Area: Malamulele Areas, Including Mangondi, Mulenzhe, Hlanganani Areas, Masia, Majozi, Tiyani, Mahatlani, Bungeni, Basani, Nwamatatani, Olifantshoek Masakona, Njhakajhaka, Nkuzana and Giyani. From 07:00 to 09:30 Area: Musina Town, Nancefield, Leeudraai, Tshipise Forever Resort, Pontdrif, Alldays, Soutpan, Bochum and Nzhelele Villages. From 23:00 to 01:30 SUNDAY – 23 FEBRUARY Load shedding will only affect the following areas: Mukondeni, Mashamba, Tshivhuyuni, Mulima, Nthabalala,Tshitale, Muwaweni, Mbhokota, Riverplats, Botlokwa, Soekmekaar. From 05:00 to 06:00